6680  return;
6681  }
6682  case Intrinsic::stacksave: {
6683  SDValue Op = getRoot();
6684  EVT VT = TLI.getValueType(DAG.getDataLayout(), I.getType());
6685  Res = DAG.getNode(ISD::STACKSAVE, sdl, DAG.getVTList(VT, MVT::Other), Op);
6686  setValue(&I, Res);
6687  DAG.setRoot(Res.getValue(1));
6688  return;
6689  }
6690  case Intrinsic::stackrestore:
6691  Res = getValue(I.getArgOperand(0));
6692  DAG.setRoot(DAG.getNode(ISD::STACKRESTORE, sdl, MVT::Other, getRoot(), Res));
6693  return;
6694  case Intrinsic::get_dynamic_area_offset: {
6695  SDValue Op = getRoot();
6696  EVT PtrTy = TLI.getFrameIndexTy(DAG.getDataLayout());
6697  EVT ResTy = TLI.getValueType(DAG.getDataLayout(), I.getType());
6698  // Result type for @llvm.get.dynamic.area.offset should match PtrTy for
6699  // target.
6700  if (PtrTy.getFixedSizeInBits() < ResTy.getFixedSizeInBits())
6701  report_fatal_error("Wrong result type for @llvm.get.dynamic.area.offset"
6702  " intrinsic!");
6703  Res = DAG.getNode(ISD::GET_DYNAMIC_AREA_OFFSET, sdl, DAG.getVTList(ResTy),
6704  Op);
6705  DAG.setRoot(Op);
6706  setValue(&I, Res);
6707  return;
6708  }
6709  case Intrinsic::stackguard: {
6710  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
6711  const Module &M = *MF.getFunction().getParent();
6712  SDValue Chain = getRoot();
6713  if (TLI.useLoadStackGuardNode()) {
6714  Res = getLoadStackGuard(DAG, sdl, Chain);
6715  } else {
6716  EVT PtrTy = TLI.getValueType(DAG.getDataLayout(), I.getType());
6717  const Value *Global = TLI.getSDagStackGuard(M);
6718  Align Align = DAG.getDataLayout().getPrefTypeAlign(Global->getType());
6719  Res = DAG.getLoad(PtrTy, sdl, Chain, getValue(Global),
6720  MachinePointerInfo(Global, 0), Align,
6721  MachineMemOperand::MOVolatile);
6722  }
6723  if (TLI.useStackGuardXorFP())
6724  Res = TLI.emitStackGuardXorFP(DAG, Res, sdl);
6725  DAG.setRoot(Chain);
6726  setValue(&I, Res);
6727  return;
6728  }
6729  case Intrinsic::stackprotector: {
6730  // Emit code into the DAG to store the stack guard onto the stack.
6731  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
6732  MachineFrameInfo &MFI = MF.getFrameInfo();
6733  SDValue Src, Chain = getRoot();
6734 
6735  if (TLI.useLoadStackGuardNode())
6736  Src = getLoadStackGuard(DAG, sdl, Chain);
6737  else
6738  Src = getValue(I.getArgOperand(0)); // The guard's value.
6739 
6740  AllocaInst *Slot = cast<AllocaInst>(I.getArgOperand(1));
6741 
6742  int FI = FuncInfo.StaticAllocaMap[Slot];
6743  MFI.setStackProtectorIndex(FI);
6744  EVT PtrTy = TLI.getFrameIndexTy(DAG.getDataLayout());
6745 
6746  SDValue FIN = DAG.getFrameIndex(FI, PtrTy);
6747 
6748  // Store the stack protector onto the stack.
6749  Res = DAG.getStore(
6750  Chain, sdl, Src, FIN,
6751  MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(DAG.getMachineFunction(), FI),
6752  MaybeAlign(), MachineMemOperand::MOVolatile);
6753  setValue(&I, Res);
6754  DAG.setRoot(Res);
6755  return;
6756  }
6757  case Intrinsic::objectsize:
6758  llvm_unreachable("llvm.objectsize.* should have been lowered already");
6759 
6760  case Intrinsic::is_constant:
6761  llvm_unreachable("llvm.is.constant.* should have been lowered already");
6762 
6763  case Intrinsic::annotation:
6764  case Intrinsic::ptr_annotation:
6765  case Intrinsic::launder_invariant_group:
6766  case Intrinsic::strip_invariant_group:
6767  // Drop the intrinsic, but forward the value
6768  setValue(&I, getValue(I.getOperand(0)));
6769  return;
6770 
6771  case Intrinsic::assume:
6772  case Intrinsic::experimental_noalias_scope_decl:
6773  case Intrinsic::var_annotation:
6774  case Intrinsic::sideeffect:
6775  // Discard annotate attributes, noalias scope declarations, assumptions, and
6776  // artificial side-effects.
6777  return;
6778 
6779  case Intrinsic::codeview_annotation: {
6780  // Emit a label associated with this metadata.
6781  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
6782  MCSymbol *Label =
6783  MF.getMMI().getContext().createTempSymbol("annotation", true);
6784  Metadata *MD = cast<MetadataAsValue>(I.getArgOperand(0))->getMetadata();
6785  MF.addCodeViewAnnotation(Label, cast<MDNode>(MD));
6786  Res = DAG.getLabelNode(ISD::ANNOTATION_LABEL, sdl, getRoot(), Label);
6787  DAG.setRoot(Res);
6788  return;
6789  }
6790 
6791  case Intrinsic::init_trampoline: {
6792  const Function *F = cast<Function>(I.getArgOperand(1)->stripPointerCasts());
6793 
6794  SDValue Ops[6];
6795  Ops[0] = getRoot();
6796  Ops[1] = getValue(I.getArgOperand(0));
6797  Ops[2] = getValue(I.getArgOperand(1));
6798  Ops[3] = getValue(I.getArgOperand(2));
6799  Ops[4] = DAG.getSrcValue(I.getArgOperand(0));
6800  Ops[5] = DAG.getSrcValue(F);
6801 
6802  Res = DAG.getNode(ISD::INIT_TRAMPOLINE, sdl, MVT::Other, Ops);
6803 
6804  DAG.setRoot(Res);
6805  return;
6806  }
6807  case Intrinsic::adjust_trampoline:
6808  setValue(&I, DAG.getNode(ISD::ADJUST_TRAMPOLINE, sdl,
6809  TLI.getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout()),
6810  getValue(I.getArgOperand(0))));
6811  return;
6812  case Intrinsic::gcroot: {
6813  assert(DAG.getMachineFunction().getFunction().hasGC() &&
6814  "only valid in functions with gc specified, enforced by Verifier");
6815  assert(GFI && "implied by previous");
6816  const Value *Alloca = I.getArgOperand(0)->stripPointerCasts();
6817  const Constant *TypeMap = cast<Constant>(I.getArgOperand(1));
6818 
6819  FrameIndexSDNode *FI = cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(getValue(Alloca).getNode());
6820  GFI->addStackRoot(FI->getIndex(), TypeMap);
6821  return;
6822  }
6823  case Intrinsic::gcread:
6824  case Intrinsic::gcwrite:
6825  llvm_unreachable("GC failed to lower gcread/gcwrite intrinsics!");
6826  case Intrinsic::get_rounding:
6827  Res = DAG.getNode(ISD::GET_ROUNDING, sdl, {MVT::i32, MVT::Other}, getRoot());
6828  setValue(&I, Res);
6829  DAG.setRoot(Res.getValue(1));
6830  return;
6831 
6832  case Intrinsic::expect:
6833  // Just replace __builtin_expect(exp, c) with EXP.
6834  setValue(&I, getValue(I.getArgOperand(0)));
6835  return;
6836 
6837  case Intrinsic::ubsantrap:
6838  case Intrinsic::debugtrap:
6839  case Intrinsic::trap: {
6840  StringRef TrapFuncName =
6841  I.getAttributes().getFnAttr("trap-func-name").getValueAsString();
6842  if (TrapFuncName.empty()) {
6843  switch (Intrinsic) {
6844  case Intrinsic::trap:
6845  DAG.setRoot(DAG.getNode(ISD::TRAP, sdl, MVT::Other, getRoot()));
6846  break;
6847  case Intrinsic::debugtrap:
6848  DAG.setRoot(DAG.getNode(ISD::DEBUGTRAP, sdl, MVT::Other, getRoot()));
6849  break;
6850  case Intrinsic::ubsantrap:
6851  DAG.setRoot(DAG.getNode(
6852  ISD::UBSANTRAP, sdl, MVT::Other, getRoot(),
6853  DAG.getTargetConstant(
6854  cast<ConstantInt>(I.getArgOperand(0))->getZExtValue(), sdl,
6855  MVT::i32)));
6856  break;
6857  default: llvm_unreachable("unknown trap intrinsic");
6858  }
6859  return;
6860  }
6861  TargetLowering::ArgListTy Args;
6862  if (Intrinsic == Intrinsic::ubsantrap) {
6863  Args.push_back(TargetLoweringBase::ArgListEntry());
6864  Args[0].Val = I.getArgOperand(0);
6865  Args[0].Node = getValue(Args[0].Val);
6866  Args[0].Ty = Args[0].Val->getType();
6867  }
6868 
6869  TargetLowering::CallLoweringInfo CLI(DAG);
6870  CLI.setDebugLoc(sdl).setChain(getRoot()).setLibCallee(
6871  CallingConv::C, I.getType(),
6872  DAG.getExternalSymbol(TrapFuncName.data(),
6873  TLI.getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout())),
6874  std::move(Args));
6875 
6876  std::pair<SDValue, SDValue> Result = TLI.LowerCallTo(CLI);
6877  DAG.setRoot(Result.second);
6878  return;
6879  }
6880 
6881  case Intrinsic::uadd_with_overflow:
6882  case Intrinsic::sadd_with_overflow:
6883  case Intrinsic::usub_with_overflow:
6884  case Intrinsic::ssub_with_overflow:
6885  case Intrinsic::umul_with_overflow:
6886  case Intrinsic::smul_with_overflow: {
6887  ISD::NodeType Op;
6888  switch (Intrinsic) {
6889  default: llvm_unreachable("Impossible intrinsic"); // Can't reach here.
6890  case Intrinsic::uadd_with_overflow: Op = ISD::UADDO; break;
6891  case Intrinsic::sadd_with_overflow: Op = ISD::SADDO; break;
6892  case Intrinsic::usub_with_overflow: Op = ISD::USUBO; break;
6893  case Intrinsic::ssub_with_overflow: Op = ISD::SSUBO; break;
6894  case Intrinsic::umul_with_overflow: Op = ISD::UMULO; break;
6895  case Intrinsic::smul_with_overflow: Op = ISD::SMULO; break;
6896  }
6897  SDValue Op1 = getValue(I.getArgOperand(0));
6898  SDValue Op2 = getValue(I.getArgOperand(1));
6899 
6900  EVT ResultVT = Op1.getValueType();
6901  EVT OverflowVT = MVT::i1;
6902  if (ResultVT.isVector())
6903  OverflowVT = EVT::getVectorVT(
6904  *Context, OverflowVT, ResultVT.getVectorElementCount());
6905 
6906  SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList(ResultVT, OverflowVT);
6907  setValue(&I, DAG.getNode(Op, sdl, VTs, Op1, Op2));
6908  return;
6909  }
6910  case Intrinsic::prefetch: {
6911  SDValue Ops[5];
6912  unsigned rw = cast<ConstantInt>(I.getArgOperand(1))->getZExtValue();
6913  auto Flags = rw == 0 ? MachineMemOperand::MOLoad :MachineMemOperand::MOStore;
6914  Ops[0] = DAG.getRoot();
6915  Ops[1] = getValue(I.getArgOperand(0));
6916  Ops[2] = getValue(I.getArgOperand(1));
6917  Ops[3] = getValue(I.getArgOperand(2));
6918  Ops[4] = getValue(I.getArgOperand(3));
6919  SDValue Result = DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(
6920  ISD::PREFETCH, sdl, DAG.getVTList(MVT::Other), Ops,
6921  EVT::getIntegerVT(*Context, 8), MachinePointerInfo(I.getArgOperand(0)),
6922  /* align */ std::nullopt, Flags);
6923 
6924  // Chain the prefetch in parallell with any pending loads, to stay out of
6925  // the way of later optimizations.
6926  PendingLoads.push_back(Result);
6927  Result = getRoot();
6928  DAG.setRoot(Result);
6929  return;
6930  }
6931  case Intrinsic::lifetime_start:
6932  case Intrinsic::lifetime_end: {
6933  bool IsStart = (Intrinsic == Intrinsic::lifetime_start);
6934  // Stack coloring is not enabled in O0, discard region information.
6935  if (TM.getOptLevel() == CodeGenOpt::None)
6936  return;
6937 
6938  const int64_t ObjectSize =
6939  cast<ConstantInt>(I.getArgOperand(0))->getSExtValue();
6940  Value *const ObjectPtr = I.getArgOperand(1);
6941  SmallVector<const Value *, 4> Allocas;
6942  getUnderlyingObjects(ObjectPtr, Allocas);
6943 
6944  for (const Value *Alloca : Allocas) {
6945  const AllocaInst *LifetimeObject = dyn_cast_or_null<AllocaInst>(Alloca);
6946 
6947  // Could not find an Alloca.
6948  if (!LifetimeObject)
6949  continue;
6950 
6951  // First check that the Alloca is static, otherwise it won't have a
6952  // valid frame index.
6953  auto SI = FuncInfo.StaticAllocaMap.find(LifetimeObject);
6954  if (SI == FuncInfo.StaticAllocaMap.end())
6955  return;
6956 
6957  const int FrameIndex = SI->second;
6958  int64_t Offset;
6959  if (GetPointerBaseWithConstantOffset(
6960  ObjectPtr, Offset, DAG.getDataLayout()) != LifetimeObject)
6961  Offset = -1; // Cannot determine offset from alloca to lifetime object.
6962  Res = DAG.getLifetimeNode(IsStart, sdl, getRoot(), FrameIndex, ObjectSize,
6963  Offset);
6964  DAG.setRoot(Res);
6965  }
6966  return;
6967  }
6968  case Intrinsic::pseudoprobe: {
6969  auto Guid = cast<ConstantInt>(I.getArgOperand(0))->getZExtValue();
6970  auto Index = cast<ConstantInt>(I.getArgOperand(1))->getZExtValue();
6971  auto Attr = cast<ConstantInt>(I.getArgOperand(2))->getZExtValue();
6972  Res = DAG.getPseudoProbeNode(sdl, getRoot(), Guid, Index, Attr);
6973  DAG.setRoot(Res);
6974  return;
6975  }
6976  case Intrinsic::invariant_start:
6977  // Discard region information.
6978  setValue(&I,
6979  DAG.getUNDEF(TLI.getValueType(DAG.getDataLayout(), I.getType())));
6980  return;
6981  case Intrinsic::invariant_end:
6982  // Discard region information.
6983  return;
6984  case Intrinsic::clear_cache:
6985  /// FunctionName may be null.
6986  if (const char *FunctionName = TLI.getClearCacheBuiltinName())
6987  lowerCallToExternalSymbol(I, FunctionName);
6988  return;
6989  case Intrinsic::donothing:
6990  case Intrinsic::seh_try_begin:
6991  case Intrinsic::seh_scope_begin:
6992  case Intrinsic::seh_try_end:
6993  case Intrinsic::seh_scope_end:
6994  // ignore
6995  return;
6996  case Intrinsic::experimental_stackmap:
6997  visitStackmap(I);
6998  return;
6999  case Intrinsic::experimental_patchpoint_void:
7000  case Intrinsic::experimental_patchpoint_i64:
7001  visitPatchpoint(I);
7002  return;
7003  case Intrinsic::experimental_gc_statepoint:
7004  LowerStatepoint(cast<GCStatepointInst>(I));
7005  return;
7006  case Intrinsic::experimental_gc_result:
7007  visitGCResult(cast<GCResultInst>(I));
7008  return;
7009  case Intrinsic::experimental_gc_relocate:
7010  visitGCRelocate(cast<GCRelocateInst>(I));
7011  return;
7012  case Intrinsic::instrprof_cover:
7013  llvm_unreachable("instrprof failed to lower a cover");
7014  case Intrinsic::instrprof_increment:
7015  llvm_unreachable("instrprof failed to lower an increment");
7016  case Intrinsic::instrprof_value_profile:
7017  llvm_unreachable("instrprof failed to lower a value profiling call");
7018  case Intrinsic::localescape: {
7019  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
7020  const TargetInstrInfo *TII = DAG.getSubtarget().getInstrInfo();
7021 
7022  // Directly emit some LOCAL_ESCAPE machine instrs. Label assignment emission
7023  // is the same on all targets.
7024  for (unsigned Idx = 0, E = I.arg_size(); Idx < E; ++Idx) {
7025  Value *Arg = I.getArgOperand(Idx)->stripPointerCasts();
7026  if (isa<ConstantPointerNull>(Arg))
7027  continue; // Skip null pointers. They represent a hole in index space.
7028  AllocaInst *Slot = cast<AllocaInst>(Arg);
7029  assert(FuncInfo.StaticAllocaMap.count(Slot) &&
7030  "can only escape static allocas");
7031  int FI = FuncInfo.StaticAllocaMap[Slot];
7032  MCSymbol *FrameAllocSym =
7033  MF.getMMI().getContext().getOrCreateFrameAllocSymbol(
7034  GlobalValue::dropLLVMManglingEscape(MF.getName()), Idx);
7035  BuildMI(*FuncInfo.MBB, FuncInfo.InsertPt, dl,
7036  TII->get(TargetOpcode::LOCAL_ESCAPE))
7037  .addSym(FrameAllocSym)
7038  .addFrameIndex(FI);
7039  }
7040 
7041  return;
7042  }
7043 
7044  case Intrinsic::localrecover: {
7045  // i8* @llvm.localrecover(i8* %fn, i8* %fp, i32 %idx)
7046  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
7047 
7048  // Get the symbol that defines the frame offset.
7049  auto *Fn = cast<Function>(I.getArgOperand(0)->stripPointerCasts());
7050  auto *Idx = cast<ConstantInt>(I.getArgOperand(2));
7051  unsigned IdxVal =
7052  unsigned(Idx->getLimitedValue(std::numeric_limits<int>::max()));
7053  MCSymbol *FrameAllocSym =
7054  MF.getMMI().getContext().getOrCreateFrameAllocSymbol(
7055  GlobalValue::dropLLVMManglingEscape(Fn->getName()), IdxVal);
7056 
7057  Value *FP = I.getArgOperand(1);
7058  SDValue FPVal = getValue(FP);
7059  EVT PtrVT = FPVal.getValueType();
7060 
7061  // Create a MCSymbol for the label to avoid any target lowering
7062  // that would make this PC relative.
7063  SDValue OffsetSym = DAG.getMCSymbol(FrameAllocSym, PtrVT);
7064  SDValue OffsetVal =
7065  DAG.getNode(ISD::LOCAL_RECOVER, sdl, PtrVT, OffsetSym);
7066 
7067  // Add the offset to the FP.
7068  SDValue Add = DAG.getMemBasePlusOffset(FPVal, OffsetVal, sdl);
7069  setValue(&I, Add);
7070 
7071  return;
7072  }
7073 
7074  case Intrinsic::eh_exceptionpointer:
7075  case Intrinsic::eh_exceptioncode: {
7076  // Get the exception pointer vreg, copy from it, and resize it to fit.
7077  const auto *CPI = cast<CatchPadInst>(I.getArgOperand(0));
7078  MVT PtrVT = TLI.getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout());
7079  const TargetRegisterClass *PtrRC = TLI.getRegClassFor(PtrVT);
7080  unsigned VReg = FuncInfo.getCatchPadExceptionPointerVReg(CPI, PtrRC);
7081  SDValue N = DAG.getCopyFromReg(DAG.getEntryNode(), sdl, VReg, PtrVT);
7082  if (Intrinsic == Intrinsic::eh_exceptioncode)
7083  N = DAG.getZExtOrTrunc(N, sdl, MVT::i32);
7084  setValue(&I, N);
7085  return;
7086  }
7087  case Intrinsic::xray_customevent: {
7088  // Here we want to make sure that the intrinsic behaves as if it has a
7089  // specific calling convention, and only for x86_64.
7090  // FIXME: Support other platforms later.
7091  const auto &Triple = DAG.getTarget().getTargetTriple();
7092  if (Triple.getArch() != Triple::x86_64)
7093  return;
7094 
7095  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Ops;
7096 
7097  // We want to say that we always want the arguments in registers.
7098  SDValue LogEntryVal = getValue(I.getArgOperand(0));
7099  SDValue StrSizeVal = getValue(I.getArgOperand(1));
7100  SDVTList NodeTys = DAG.getVTList(MVT::Other, MVT::Glue);
7101  SDValue Chain = getRoot();
7102  Ops.push_back(LogEntryVal);
7103  Ops.push_back(StrSizeVal);
7104  Ops.push_back(Chain);
7105 
7106  // We need to enforce the calling convention for the callsite, so that
7107  // argument ordering is enforced correctly, and that register allocation can
7108  // see that some registers may be assumed clobbered and have to preserve
7109  // them across calls to the intrinsic.
7110  MachineSDNode *MN = DAG.getMachineNode(TargetOpcode::PATCHABLE_EVENT_CALL,
7111  sdl, NodeTys, Ops);
7112  SDValue patchableNode = SDValue(MN, 0);
7113  DAG.setRoot(patchableNode);
7114  setValue(&I, patchableNode);
7115  return;
7116  }
7117  case Intrinsic::xray_typedevent: {
7118  // Here we want to make sure that the intrinsic behaves as if it has a
7119  // specific calling convention, and only for x86_64.
7120  // FIXME: Support other platforms later.
7121  const auto &Triple = DAG.getTarget().getTargetTriple();
7122  if (Triple.getArch() != Triple::x86_64)
7123  return;
7124 
7125  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Ops;
7126 
7127  // We want to say that we always want the arguments in registers.
7128  // It's unclear to me how manipulating the selection DAG here forces callers
7129  // to provide arguments in registers instead of on the stack.
7130  SDValue LogTypeId = getValue(I.getArgOperand(0));
7131  SDValue LogEntryVal = getValue(I.getArgOperand(1));
7132  SDValue StrSizeVal = getValue(I.getArgOperand(2));
7133  SDVTList NodeTys = DAG.getVTList(MVT::Other, MVT::Glue);
7134  SDValue Chain = getRoot();
7135  Ops.push_back(LogTypeId);
7136  Ops.push_back(LogEntryVal);
7137  Ops.push_back(StrSizeVal);
7138  Ops.push_back(Chain);
7139 
7140  // We need to enforce the calling convention for the callsite, so that
7141  // argument ordering is enforced correctly, and that register allocation can
7142  // see that some registers may be assumed clobbered and have to preserve
7143  // them across calls to the intrinsic.
7144  MachineSDNode *MN = DAG.getMachineNode(
7145  TargetOpcode::PATCHABLE_TYPED_EVENT_CALL, sdl, NodeTys, Ops);
7146  SDValue patchableNode = SDValue(MN, 0);
7147  DAG.setRoot(patchableNode);
7148  setValue(&I, patchableNode);
7149  return;
7150  }
7151  case Intrinsic::experimental_deoptimize:
7152  LowerDeoptimizeCall(&I);
7153  return;
7154  case Intrinsic::experimental_stepvector:
7155  visitStepVector(I);
7156  return;
7157  case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_fadd:
7158  case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_fmul:
7159  case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_add:
7160  case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_mul:
7161  case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_and:
7162  case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_or:
7163  case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_xor:
7164  case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_smax:
7165  case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_smin:
7166  case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_umax:
7167  case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_umin:
7168  case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_fmax:
7169  case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_fmin:
7170  visitVectorReduce(I, Intrinsic);
7171  return;
7172 
7173  case Intrinsic::icall_branch_funnel: {
7174  SmallVector<SDValue, 16> Ops;
7175  Ops.push_back(getValue(I.getArgOperand(0)));
7176 
7177  int64_t Offset;
7178  auto *Base = dyn_cast<GlobalObject>(GetPointerBaseWithConstantOffset(
7179  I.getArgOperand(1), Offset, DAG.getDataLayout()));
7180  if (!Base)
7181  report_fatal_error(
7182  "llvm.icall.branch.funnel operand must be a GlobalValue");
7183  Ops.push_back(DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(Base, sdl, MVT::i64, 0));
7184 
7185  struct BranchFunnelTarget {
7186  int64_t Offset;
7187  SDValue Target;
7188  };
7189  SmallVector<BranchFunnelTarget, 8> Targets;
7190 
7191  for (unsigned Op = 1, N = I.arg_size(); Op != N; Op += 2) {
7192  auto *ElemBase = dyn_cast<GlobalObject>(GetPointerBaseWithConstantOffset(
7193  I.getArgOperand(Op), Offset, DAG.getDataLayout()));
7194  if (ElemBase != Base)
7195  report_fatal_error("all llvm.icall.branch.funnel operands must refer "
7196  "to the same GlobalValue");
7197 
7198  SDValue Val = getValue(I.getArgOperand(Op + 1));
7199  auto *GA = dyn_cast<GlobalAddressSDNode>(Val);
7200  if (!GA)
7201  report_fatal_error(
7202  "llvm.icall.branch.funnel operand must be a GlobalValue");
7203  Targets.push_back({Offset, DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(
7204  GA->getGlobal(), sdl, Val.getValueType(),
7205  GA->getOffset())});
7206  }
7207  llvm::sort(Targets,
7208  [](const BranchFunnelTarget &T1, const BranchFunnelTarget &T2) {
7209  return T1.Offset < T2.Offset;
7210  });
7211 
7212  for (auto &T : Targets) {
7213  Ops.push_back(DAG.getTargetConstant(T.Offset, sdl, MVT::i32));
7214  Ops.push_back(T.Target);
7215  }
7216 
7217  Ops.push_back(DAG.getRoot()); // Chain
7218  SDValue N(DAG.getMachineNode(TargetOpcode::ICALL_BRANCH_FUNNEL, sdl,
7219  MVT::Other, Ops),
7220  0);
7221  DAG.setRoot(N);
7222  setValue(&I, N);
7223  HasTailCall = true;
7224  return;
7225  }
7226 
7227  case Intrinsic::wasm_landingpad_index:
7228  // Information this intrinsic contained has been transferred to
7229  // MachineFunction in SelectionDAGISel::PrepareEHLandingPad. We can safely
7230  // delete it now.
7231  return;
7232 
7233  case Intrinsic::aarch64_settag:
7234  case Intrinsic::aarch64_settag_zero: {
7235  const SelectionDAGTargetInfo &TSI = DAG.getSelectionDAGInfo();
7236  bool ZeroMemory = Intrinsic == Intrinsic::aarch64_settag_zero;
7237  SDValue Val = TSI.EmitTargetCodeForSetTag(
7238  DAG, sdl, getRoot(), getValue(I.getArgOperand(0)),
7239  getValue(I.getArgOperand(1)), MachinePointerInfo(I.getArgOperand(0)),
7240  ZeroMemory);
7241  DAG.setRoot(Val);
7242  setValue(&I, Val);
7243  return;
7244  }
7245  case Intrinsic::ptrmask: {
7246  SDValue Ptr = getValue(I.getOperand(0));
7247  SDValue Const = getValue(I.getOperand(1));
7248 
7249  EVT PtrVT = Ptr.getValueType();
7250  setValue(&I, DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, sdl, PtrVT, Ptr,
7251  DAG.getZExtOrTrunc(Const, sdl, PtrVT)));
7252  return;
7253  }
7254  case Intrinsic::threadlocal_address: {
7255  setValue(&I, getValue(I.getOperand(0)));
7256  return;
7257  }
7258  case Intrinsic::get_active_lane_mask: {
7259  EVT CCVT = TLI.getValueType(DAG.getDataLayout(), I.getType());
7260  SDValue Index = getValue(I.getOperand(0));
7261  EVT ElementVT = Index.getValueType();
7262 
7263  if (!TLI.shouldExpandGetActiveLaneMask(CCVT, ElementVT)) {
7264  visitTargetIntrinsic(I, Intrinsic);
7265  return;
7266  }
7267 
7268  SDValue TripCount = getValue(I.getOperand(1));
7269  auto VecTy = CCVT.changeVectorElementType(ElementVT);
7270 
7271  SDValue VectorIndex = DAG.getSplat(VecTy, sdl, Index);
7272  SDValue VectorTripCount = DAG.getSplat(VecTy, sdl, TripCount);
7273  SDValue VectorStep = DAG.getStepVector(sdl, VecTy);
7274  SDValue VectorInduction = DAG.getNode(
7275  ISD::UADDSAT, sdl, VecTy, VectorIndex, VectorStep);
7276  SDValue SetCC = DAG.getSetCC(sdl, CCVT, VectorInduction,
7277  VectorTripCount, ISD::CondCode::SETULT);
7278  setValue(&I, SetCC);
7279  return;
7280  }
7281  case Intrinsic::vector_insert: {
7282  SDValue Vec = getValue(I.getOperand(0));
7283  SDValue SubVec = getValue(I.getOperand(1));
7284  SDValue Index = getValue(I.getOperand(2));
7285 
7286  // The intrinsic's index type is i64, but the SDNode requires an index type
7287  // suitable for the target. Convert the index as required.
7288  MVT VectorIdxTy = TLI.getVectorIdxTy(DAG.getDataLayout());
7289  if (Index.getValueType() != VectorIdxTy)
7290  Index = DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(
7291  cast<ConstantSDNode>(Index)->getZExtValue(), sdl);
7292 
7293  EVT ResultVT = TLI.getValueType(DAG.getDataLayout(), I.getType());
7294  setValue(&I, DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR, sdl, ResultVT, Vec, SubVec,
7295  Index));
7296  return;
7297  }
7298  case Intrinsic::vector_extract: {
7299  SDValue Vec = getValue(I.getOperand(0));
7300  SDValue Index = getValue(I.getOperand(1));
7301  EVT ResultVT = TLI.getValueType(DAG.getDataLayout(), I.getType());
7302 
7303  // The intrinsic's index type is i64, but the SDNode requires an index type
7304  // suitable for the target. Convert the index as required.
7305  MVT VectorIdxTy = TLI.getVectorIdxTy(DAG.getDataLayout());
7306  if (Index.getValueType() != VectorIdxTy)
7307  Index = DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(
7308  cast<ConstantSDNode>(Index)->getZExtValue(), sdl);
7309 
7310  setValue(&I,
7311  DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, sdl, ResultVT, Vec, Index));
7312  return;
7313  }
7314  case Intrinsic::experimental_vector_reverse:
7315  visitVectorReverse(I);
7316  return;
7317  case Intrinsic::experimental_vector_splice:
7318  visitVectorSplice(I);
7319  return;
7320  }
7321 }
7322 
7323 void SelectionDAGBuilder::visitConstrainedFPIntrinsic(
7324  const ConstrainedFPIntrinsic &FPI) {
7325  SDLoc sdl = getCurSDLoc();
7326 
7327  // We do not need to serialize constrained FP intrinsics against
7328  // each other or against (nonvolatile) loads, so they can be
7329  // chained like loads.
7330  SDValue Chain = DAG.getRoot();
7331  SmallVector<SDValue, 4> Opers;
7332  Opers.push_back(Chain);
7333  if (FPI.isUnaryOp()) {
7334  Opers.push_back(getValue(FPI.getArgOperand(0)));
7335  } else if (FPI.isTernaryOp()) {
7336  Opers.push_back(getValue(FPI.getArgOperand(0)));
7337  Opers.push_back(getValue(FPI.getArgOperand(1)));
7338  Opers.push_back(getValue(FPI.getArgOperand(2)));
7339  } else {
7340  Opers.push_back(getValue(FPI.getArgOperand(0)));
7341  Opers.push_back(getValue(FPI.getArgOperand(1)));
7342  }
7343 
7344  auto pushOutChain = [this](SDValue Result, fp::ExceptionBehavior EB) {
7345  assert(Result.getNode()->getNumValues() == 2);
7346 
7347  // Push node to the appropriate list so that future instructions can be
7348  // chained up correctly.
7349  SDValue OutChain = Result.getValue(1);
7350  switch (EB) {
7351  case fp::ExceptionBehavior::ebIgnore:
7352  // The only reason why ebIgnore nodes still need to be chained is that
7353  // they might depend on the current rounding mode, and therefore must
7354  // not be moved across instruction that may change that mode.
7355  [[fallthrough]];
7356  case fp::ExceptionBehavior::ebMayTrap:
7357  // These must not be moved across calls or instructions that may change
7358  // floating-point exception masks.
7359  PendingConstrainedFP.push_back(OutChain);
7360  break;
7361  case fp::ExceptionBehavior::ebStrict:
7362  // These must not be moved across calls or instructions that may change
7363  // floating-point exception masks or read floating-point exception flags.
7364  // In addition, they cannot be optimized out even if unused.
7365  PendingConstrainedFPStrict.push_back(OutChain);
7366  break;
7367  }
7368  };
7369 
7370  const TargetLowering &TLI = DAG.getTargetLoweringInfo();
7371  EVT VT = TLI.getValueType(DAG.getDataLayout(), FPI.getType());
7372  SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList(VT, MVT::Other);
7373  fp::ExceptionBehavior EB = *FPI.getExceptionBehavior();
7374 
7375  SDNodeFlags Flags;
7376  if (EB == fp::ExceptionBehavior::ebIgnore)
7377  Flags.setNoFPExcept(true);
7378 
7379  if (auto *FPOp = dyn_cast<FPMathOperator>(&FPI))
7380  Flags.copyFMF(*FPOp);
7381 
7382  unsigned Opcode;
7383  switch (FPI.getIntrinsicID()) {
7384  default: llvm_unreachable("Impossible intrinsic"); // Can't reach here.
7385 #define DAG_INSTRUCTION(NAME, NARG, ROUND_MODE, INTRINSIC, DAGN) \
7386  case Intrinsic::INTRINSIC: \
7387  Opcode = ISD::STRICT_##DAGN; \
7388  break;
7389 #include "llvm/IR/ConstrainedOps.def"
7390  case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_fmuladd: {
7391  Opcode = ISD::STRICT_FMA;
7392  // Break fmuladd into fmul and fadd.
7393  if (TM.Options.AllowFPOpFusion == FPOpFusion::Strict ||
7394  !TLI.isFMAFasterThanFMulAndFAdd(DAG.getMachineFunction(), VT)) {
7395  Opers.pop_back();
7396  SDValue Mul = DAG.getNode(ISD::STRICT_FMUL, sdl, VTs, Opers, Flags);
7397  pushOutChain(Mul, EB);
7398  Opcode = ISD::STRICT_FADD;
7399  Opers.clear();
7400  Opers.push_back(Mul.getValue(1));
7401  Opers.push_back(Mul.getValue(0));
7402  Opers.push_back(getValue(FPI.getArgOperand(2)));
7403  }
7404  break;
7405  }
7406  }
7407 
7408  // A few strict DAG nodes carry additional operands that are not
7409  // set up by the default code above.
7410  switch (Opcode) {
7411  default: break;
7412  case ISD::STRICT_FP_ROUND:
7413  Opers.push_back(
7414  DAG.getTargetConstant(0, sdl, TLI.getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout())));
7415  break;
7416  case ISD::STRICT_FSETCC:
7417  case ISD::STRICT_FSETCCS: {
7418  auto *FPCmp = dyn_cast<ConstrainedFPCmpIntrinsic>(&FPI);
7419  ISD::CondCode Condition = getFCmpCondCode(FPCmp->getPredicate());
7420  if (TM.Options.NoNaNsFPMath)
7421  Condition = getFCmpCodeWithoutNaN(Condition);
7422  Opers.push_back(DAG.getCondCode(Condition));
7423  break;
7424  }
7425  }
7426 
7427  SDValue Result = DAG.getNode(Opcode, sdl, VTs, Opers, Flags);
7428  pushOutChain(Result, EB);
7429 
7430  SDValue FPResult = Result.getValue(0);
7431  setValue(&FPI, FPResult);
7432 }
7433 
7434 static unsigned getISDForVPIntrinsic(const VPIntrinsic &VPIntrin) {
7435  std::optional<unsigned> ResOPC;
7436  switch (VPIntrin.getIntrinsicID()) {
7437  case Intrinsic::vp_ctlz: {
7438  bool IsZeroUndef = cast<ConstantInt>(VPIntrin.getArgOperand(3))->isOne();
7439  ResOPC = IsZeroUndef ? ISD::VP_CTLZ_ZERO_UNDEF : ISD::VP_CTLZ;
7440  break;
7441  }
7442  case Intrinsic::vp_cttz: {
7443  bool IsZeroUndef = cast<ConstantInt>(VPIntrin.getArgOperand(3))->isOne();
7444  ResOPC = IsZeroUndef ? ISD::VP_CTTZ_ZERO_UNDEF : ISD::VP_CTTZ;
7445  break;
7446  }
7447 #define HELPER_MAP_VPID_TO_VPSD(VPID, VPSD) \
7448  case Intrinsic::VPID: \
7449  ResOPC = ISD::VPSD; \
7450  break;
7451 #include "llvm/IR/VPIntrinsics.def"
7452  }
7453 
7454  if (!ResOPC)
7455  llvm_unreachable(
7456  "Inconsistency: no SDNode available for this VPIntrinsic!");
7457 
7458  if (*ResOPC == ISD::VP_REDUCE_SEQ_FADD ||
7459  *ResOPC == ISD::VP_REDUCE_SEQ_FMUL) {
7460  if (VPIntrin.getFastMathFlags().allowReassoc())
7461  return *ResOPC == ISD::VP_REDUCE_SEQ_FADD ? ISD::VP_REDUCE_FADD
7462  : ISD::VP_REDUCE_FMUL;
7463  }
7464 
7465  return *ResOPC;
7466 }
7467 
7468 void SelectionDAGBuilder::visitVPLoad(const VPIntrinsic &VPIntrin, EVT VT,
7469  SmallVector<SDValue, 7> &OpValues) {
7470  SDLoc DL = getCurSDLoc();
7471  Value *PtrOperand = VPIntrin.getArgOperand(0);
7472  MaybeAlign Alignment = VPIntrin.getPointerAlignment();
7473  AAMDNodes AAInfo = VPIntrin.getAAMetadata();
7474  const MDNode *Ranges = VPIntrin.getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_range);
7475  SDValue LD;
7476  bool AddToChain = true;
7477  // Do not serialize variable-length loads of constant memory with
7478  // anything.
7479  if (!Alignment)
7480  Alignment = DAG.getEVTAlign(VT);
7481  MemoryLocation ML = MemoryLocation::getAfter(PtrOperand, AAInfo);
7482  AddToChain = !AA || !AA->pointsToConstantMemory(ML);
7483  SDValue InChain = AddToChain ? DAG.getRoot() : DAG.getEntryNode();
7484  MachineMemOperand *MMO = DAG.getMachineFunction().getMachineMemOperand(
7485  MachinePointerInfo(PtrOperand), MachineMemOperand::MOLoad,
7486  MemoryLocation::UnknownSize, *Alignment, AAInfo, Ranges);
7487  LD = DAG.getLoadVP(VT, DL, InChain, OpValues[0], OpValues[1], OpValues[2],
7488  MMO, false /*IsExpanding */);
7489  if (AddToChain)
7490  PendingLoads.push_back(LD.getValue(1));
7491  setValue(&VPIntrin, LD);
7492 }
7493 
7494 void SelectionDAGBuilder::visitVPGather(const VPIntrinsic &VPIntrin, EVT VT,
7495  SmallVector<SDValue, 7> &OpValues) {
7496  SDLoc DL = getCurSDLoc();
7497  const TargetLowering &TLI = DAG.getTargetLoweringInfo();
7498  Value *PtrOperand = VPIntrin.getArgOperand(0);
7499  MaybeAlign Alignment = VPIntrin.getPointerAlignment();
7500  AAMDNodes AAInfo = VPIntrin.getAAMetadata();
7501  const MDNode *Ranges = VPIntrin.getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_range);
7502  SDValue LD;
7503  if (!Alignment)
7504  Alignment = DAG.getEVTAlign(VT.getScalarType());
7505  unsigned AS =
7506  PtrOperand->getType()->getScalarType()->getPointerAddressSpace();
7507  MachineMemOperand *MMO = DAG.getMachineFunction().getMachineMemOperand(
7508  MachinePointerInfo(AS), MachineMemOperand::MOLoad,
7509  MemoryLocation::UnknownSize, *Alignment, AAInfo, Ranges);
7510  SDValue Base, Index, Scale;
7511  ISD::MemIndexType IndexType;
7512  bool UniformBase = getUniformBase(PtrOperand, Base, Index, IndexType, Scale,
7513  this, VPIntrin.getParent(),
7514  VT.getScalarStoreSize());
7515  if (!UniformBase) {
7516  Base = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, TLI.getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout()));
7517  Index = getValue(PtrOperand);
7518  IndexType = ISD::SIGNED_SCALED;
7519  Scale = DAG.getTargetConstant(1, DL, TLI.getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout()));
7520  }
7521  EVT IdxVT = Index.getValueType();
7522  EVT EltTy = IdxVT.getVectorElementType();
7523  if (TLI.shouldExtendGSIndex(IdxVT, EltTy)) {
7524  EVT NewIdxVT = IdxVT.changeVectorElementType(EltTy);
7525  Index = DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND, DL, NewIdxVT, Index);
7526  }
7527  LD = DAG.getGatherVP(
7528  DAG.getVTList(VT, MVT::Other), VT, DL,
7529  {DAG.getRoot(), Base, Index, Scale, OpValues[1], OpValues[2]}, MMO,
7530  IndexType);
7531  PendingLoads.push_back(LD.getValue(1));
7532  setValue(&VPIntrin, LD);
7533 }
7534 
7535 void SelectionDAGBuilder::visitVPStore(const VPIntrinsic &VPIntrin,
7536  SmallVector<SDValue, 7> &OpValues) {
7537  SDLoc DL = getCurSDLoc();
7538  Value *PtrOperand = VPIntrin.getArgOperand(1);
7539  EVT VT = OpValues[0].getValueType();
7540  MaybeAlign Alignment = VPIntrin.getPointerAlignment();
7541  AAMDNodes AAInfo = VPIntrin.getAAMetadata();
7542  SDValue ST;
7543  if (!Alignment)
7544  Alignment = DAG.getEVTAlign(VT);
7545  SDValue Ptr = OpValues[1];
7546  SDValue Offset = DAG.getUNDEF(Ptr.getValueType());
7547  MachineMemOperand *MMO = DAG.getMachineFunction().getMachineMemOperand(
7548  MachinePointerInfo(PtrOperand), MachineMemOperand::MOStore,
7549  MemoryLocation::UnknownSize, *Alignment, AAInfo);
7550  ST = DAG.getStoreVP(getMemoryRoot(), DL, OpValues[0], Ptr, Offset,
7551  OpValues[2], OpValues[3], VT, MMO, ISD::UNINDEXED,
7552  /* IsTruncating */ false, /*IsCompressing*/ false);
7553  DAG.setRoot(ST);
7554  setValue(&VPIntrin, ST);
7555 }
7556 
7557 void SelectionDAGBuilder::visitVPScatter(const VPIntrinsic &VPIntrin,
7558  SmallVector<SDValue, 7> &OpValues) {
7559  SDLoc DL = getCurSDLoc();
7560  const TargetLowering &TLI = DAG.getTargetLoweringInfo();
7561  Value *PtrOperand = VPIntrin.getArgOperand(1);
7562  EVT VT = OpValues[0].getValueType();
7563  MaybeAlign Alignment = VPIntrin.getPointerAlignment();
7564  AAMDNodes AAInfo = VPIntrin.getAAMetadata();
7565  SDValue ST;
7566  if (!Alignment)
7567  Alignment = DAG.getEVTAlign(VT.getScalarType());
7568  unsigned AS =
7569  PtrOperand->getType()->getScalarType()->getPointerAddressSpace();
7570  MachineMemOperand *MMO = DAG.getMachineFunction().getMachineMemOperand(
7571  MachinePointerInfo(AS), MachineMemOperand::MOStore,
7572  MemoryLocation::UnknownSize, *Alignment, AAInfo);
7573  SDValue Base, Index, Scale;
7574  ISD::MemIndexType IndexType;
7575  bool UniformBase = getUniformBase(PtrOperand, Base, Index, IndexType, Scale,
7576  this, VPIntrin.getParent(),
7577  VT.getScalarStoreSize());
7578  if (!UniformBase) {
7579  Base = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, TLI.getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout()));
7580  Index = getValue(PtrOperand);
7581  IndexType = ISD::SIGNED_SCALED;
7582  Scale =
7583  DAG.getTargetConstant(1, DL, TLI.getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout()));
7584  }
7585  EVT IdxVT = Index.getValueType();
7586  EVT EltTy = IdxVT.getVectorElementType();
7587  if (TLI.shouldExtendGSIndex(IdxVT, EltTy)) {
7588  EVT NewIdxVT = IdxVT.changeVectorElementType(EltTy);
7589  Index = DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND, DL, NewIdxVT, Index);
7590  }
7591  ST = DAG.getScatterVP(DAG.getVTList(MVT::Other), VT, DL,
7592  {getMemoryRoot(), OpValues[0], Base, Index, Scale,
7593  OpValues[2], OpValues[3]},
7594  MMO, IndexType);
7595  DAG.setRoot(ST);
7596  setValue(&VPIntrin, ST);
7597 }
7598 
7599 void SelectionDAGBuilder::visitVPStridedLoad(
7600  const VPIntrinsic &VPIntrin, EVT VT, SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &OpValues) {
7601  SDLoc DL = getCurSDLoc();
7602  Value *PtrOperand = VPIntrin.getArgOperand(0);
7603  MaybeAlign Alignment = VPIntrin.getPointerAlignment();
7604  if (!Alignment)
7605  Alignment = DAG.getEVTAlign(VT.getScalarType());
7606  AAMDNodes AAInfo = VPIntrin.getAAMetadata();
7607  const MDNode *Ranges = VPIntrin.getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_range);
7608  MemoryLocation ML = MemoryLocation::getAfter(PtrOperand, AAInfo);
7609  bool AddToChain = !AA || !AA->pointsToConstantMemory(ML);
7610  SDValue InChain = AddToChain ? DAG.getRoot() : DAG.getEntryNode();
7611  MachineMemOperand *MMO = DAG.getMachineFunction().getMachineMemOperand(
7612  MachinePointerInfo(PtrOperand), MachineMemOperand::MOLoad,
7613  MemoryLocation::UnknownSize, *Alignment, AAInfo, Ranges);
7614 
7615  SDValue LD = DAG.getStridedLoadVP(VT, DL, InChain, OpValues[0], OpValues[1],
7616  OpValues[2], OpValues[3], MMO,
7617  false /*IsExpanding*/);
7618 
7619  if (AddToChain)
7620  PendingLoads.push_back(LD.getValue(1));
7621  setValue(&VPIntrin, LD);
7622 }
7623 
7624 void SelectionDAGBuilder::visitVPStridedStore(
7625  const VPIntrinsic &VPIntrin, SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &OpValues) {
7626  SDLoc DL = getCurSDLoc();
7627  Value *PtrOperand = VPIntrin.getArgOperand(1);
7628  EVT VT = OpValues[0].getValueType();
7629  MaybeAlign Alignment = VPIntrin.getPointerAlignment();
7630  if (!Alignment)
7631  Alignment = DAG.getEVTAlign(VT.getScalarType());
7632  AAMDNodes AAInfo = VPIntrin.getAAMetadata();
7633  MachineMemOperand *MMO = DAG.getMachineFunction().getMachineMemOperand(
7634  MachinePointerInfo(PtrOperand), MachineMemOperand::MOStore,
7635  MemoryLocation::UnknownSize, *Alignment, AAInfo);
7636 
7637  SDValue ST = DAG.getStridedStoreVP(
7638  getMemoryRoot(), DL, OpValues[0], OpValues[1],
7639  DAG.getUNDEF(OpValues[1].getValueType()), OpValues[2], OpValues[3],
7640  OpValues[4], VT, MMO, ISD::UNINDEXED, /*IsTruncating*/ false,
7641  /*IsCompressing*/ false);
7642 
7643  DAG.setRoot(ST);
7644  setValue(&VPIntrin, ST);
7645 }
7646 
7647 void SelectionDAGBuilder::visitVPCmp(const VPCmpIntrinsic &VPIntrin) {
7648  const TargetLowering &TLI = DAG.getTargetLoweringInfo();
7649  SDLoc DL = getCurSDLoc();
7650 
7651  ISD::CondCode Condition;
7652  CmpInst::Predicate CondCode = VPIntrin.getPredicate();
7653  bool IsFP = VPIntrin.getOperand(0)->getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy();
7654  if (IsFP) {
7655  // FIXME: Regular fcmps are FPMathOperators which may have fast-math (nnan)
7656  // flags, but calls that don't return floating-point types can't be
7657  // FPMathOperators, like vp.fcmp. This affects constrained fcmp too.
7658  Condition = getFCmpCondCode(CondCode);
7659  if (TM.Options.NoNaNsFPMath)
7660  Condition = getFCmpCodeWithoutNaN(Condition);
7661  } else {
7662  Condition = getICmpCondCode(CondCode);
7663  }
7664 
7665  SDValue Op1 = getValue(VPIntrin.getOperand(0));
7666  SDValue Op2 = getValue(VPIntrin.getOperand(1));
7667  // #2 is the condition code
7668  SDValue MaskOp = getValue(VPIntrin.getOperand(3));
7669  SDValue EVL = getValue(VPIntrin.getOperand(4));
7670  MVT EVLParamVT = TLI.getVPExplicitVectorLengthTy();
7671  assert(EVLParamVT.isScalarInteger() && EVLParamVT.bitsGE(MVT::i32) &&
7672  "Unexpected target EVL type");
7673  EVL = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, DL, EVLParamVT, EVL);
7674 
7675  EVT DestVT = DAG.getTargetLoweringInfo().getValueType(DAG.getDataLayout(),
7676  VPIntrin.getType());
7677  setValue(&VPIntrin,
7678  DAG.getSetCCVP(DL, DestVT, Op1, Op2, Condition, MaskOp, EVL));
7679 }
7680 
7681 void SelectionDAGBuilder::visitVectorPredicationIntrinsic(
7682  const VPIntrinsic &VPIntrin) {
7683  SDLoc DL = getCurSDLoc();
7684  unsigned Opcode = getISDForVPIntrinsic(VPIntrin);
7685 
7686  auto IID = VPIntrin.getIntrinsicID();
7687 
7688  if (const auto *CmpI = dyn_cast<VPCmpIntrinsic>(&VPIntrin))
7689  return visitVPCmp(*CmpI);
7690 
7691  SmallVector<EVT, 4> ValueVTs;
7692  const TargetLowering &TLI = DAG.getTargetLoweringInfo();
7693  ComputeValueVTs(TLI, DAG.getDataLayout(), VPIntrin.getType(), ValueVTs);
7694  SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList(ValueVTs);
7695 
7696  auto EVLParamPos = VPIntrinsic::getVectorLengthParamPos(IID);
7697 
7698  MVT EVLParamVT = TLI.getVPExplicitVectorLengthTy();
7699  assert(EVLParamVT.isScalarInteger() && EVLParamVT.bitsGE(MVT::i32) &&
7700  "Unexpected target EVL type");
7701 
7702  // Request operands.
7703  SmallVector<SDValue, 7> OpValues;
7704  for (unsigned I = 0; I < VPIntrin.arg_size(); ++I) {
7705  auto Op = getValue(VPIntrin.getArgOperand(I));
7706  if (I == EVLParamPos)
7707  Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, DL, EVLParamVT, Op);
7708  OpValues.push_back(Op);
7709  }
7710 
7711  switch (Opcode) {
7712  default: {
7713  SDNodeFlags SDFlags;
7714  if (auto *FPMO = dyn_cast<FPMathOperator>(&VPIntrin))
7715  SDFlags.copyFMF(*FPMO);
7716  SDValue Result = DAG.getNode(Opcode, DL, VTs, OpValues, SDFlags);
7717  setValue(&VPIntrin, Result);
7718  break;
7719  }
7720  case ISD::VP_LOAD:
7721  visitVPLoad(VPIntrin, ValueVTs[0], OpValues);
7722  break;
7723  case ISD::VP_GATHER:
7724  visitVPGather(VPIntrin, ValueVTs[0], OpValues);
7725  break;
7726  case ISD::EXPERIMENTAL_VP_STRIDED_LOAD:
7727  visitVPStridedLoad(VPIntrin, ValueVTs[0], OpValues);
7728  break;
7729  case ISD::VP_STORE:
7730  visitVPStore(VPIntrin, OpValues);
7731  break;
7732  case ISD::VP_SCATTER:
7733  visitVPScatter(VPIntrin, OpValues);
7734  break;
7735  case ISD::EXPERIMENTAL_VP_STRIDED_STORE:
7736  visitVPStridedStore(VPIntrin, OpValues);
7737  break;
7738  case ISD::VP_FMULADD: {
7739  assert(OpValues.size() == 5 && "Unexpected number of operands");
7740  SDNodeFlags SDFlags;
7741  if (auto *FPMO = dyn_cast<FPMathOperator>(&VPIntrin))
7742  SDFlags.copyFMF(*FPMO);
7743  if (TM.Options.AllowFPOpFusion != FPOpFusion::Strict &&
7744  TLI.isFMAFasterThanFMulAndFAdd(DAG.getMachineFunction(), ValueVTs[0])) {
7745  setValue(&VPIntrin, DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_FMA, DL, VTs, OpValues, SDFlags));
7746  } else {
7747  SDValue Mul = DAG.getNode(
7748  ISD::VP_FMUL, DL, VTs,
7749  {OpValues[0], OpValues[1], OpValues[3], OpValues[4]}, SDFlags);
7750  SDValue Add =
7751  DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_FADD, DL, VTs,
7752  {Mul, OpValues[2], OpValues[3], OpValues[4]}, SDFlags);
7753  setValue(&VPIntrin, Add);
7754  }
7755  break;
7756  }
7757  case ISD::VP_INTTOPTR: {
7758  SDValue N = OpValues[0];
7759  EVT DestVT = TLI.getValueType(DAG.getDataLayout(), VPIntrin.getType());
7760  EVT PtrMemVT = TLI.getMemValueType(DAG.getDataLayout(), VPIntrin.getType());
7761  N = DAG.getVPPtrExtOrTrunc(getCurSDLoc(), DestVT, N, OpValues[1],
7762  OpValues[2]);
7763  N = DAG.getVPZExtOrTrunc(getCurSDLoc(), PtrMemVT, N, OpValues[1],
7764  OpValues[2]);
7765  setValue(&VPIntrin, N);
7766  break;
7767  }
7768  case ISD::VP_PTRTOINT: {
7769  SDValue N = OpValues[0];
7770  EVT DestVT = DAG.getTargetLoweringInfo().getValueType(DAG.getDataLayout(),
7771  VPIntrin.getType());
7772  EVT PtrMemVT = TLI.getMemValueType(DAG.getDataLayout(),
7773  VPIntrin.getOperand(0)->getType());
7774  N = DAG.getVPPtrExtOrTrunc(getCurSDLoc(), PtrMemVT, N, OpValues[1],
7775  OpValues[2]);
7776  N = DAG.getVPZExtOrTrunc(getCurSDLoc(), DestVT, N, OpValues[1],
7777  OpValues[2]);
7778  setValue(&VPIntrin, N);
7779  break;
7780  }
7781  case ISD::VP_ABS:
7782  case ISD::VP_CTLZ:
7783  case ISD::VP_CTLZ_ZERO_UNDEF:
7784  case ISD::VP_CTTZ:
7785  case ISD::VP_CTTZ_ZERO_UNDEF: {
7786  // Pop is_zero_poison operand for cp.ctlz/cttz or
7787  // is_int_min_poison operand for vp.abs.
7788  OpValues.pop_back();
7789  SDValue Result = DAG.getNode(Opcode, DL, VTs, OpValues);
7790  setValue(&VPIntrin, Result);
7791  break;
7792  }
7793  }
7794 }
7795 
7796 SDValue SelectionDAGBuilder::lowerStartEH(SDValue Chain,
7797  const BasicBlock *EHPadBB,
7798  MCSymbol *&BeginLabel) {
7799  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
7800  MachineModuleInfo &MMI = MF.getMMI();
7801 
7802  // Insert a label before the invoke call to mark the try range. This can be
7803  // used to detect deletion of the invoke via the MachineModuleInfo.
7804  BeginLabel = MMI.getContext().createTempSymbol();
7805 
7806  // For SjLj, keep track of which landing pads go with which invokes
7807  // so as to maintain the ordering of pads in the LSDA.
7808  unsigned CallSiteIndex = MMI.getCurrentCallSite();
7809  if (CallSiteIndex) {
7810  MF.setCallSiteBeginLabel(BeginLabel, CallSiteIndex);
7811  LPadToCallSiteMap[FuncInfo.MBBMap[EHPadBB]].push_back(CallSiteIndex);
7812 
7813  // Now that the call site is handled, stop tracking it.
7814  MMI.setCurrentCallSite(0);
7815  }
7816 
7817  return DAG.getEHLabel(getCurSDLoc(), Chain, BeginLabel);
7818 }
7819 
7820 SDValue SelectionDAGBuilder::lowerEndEH(SDValue Chain, const InvokeInst *II,
7821  const BasicBlock *EHPadBB,
7822  MCSymbol *BeginLabel) {
7823  assert(BeginLabel && "BeginLabel should've been set");
7824 
7825  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
7826  MachineModuleInfo &MMI = MF.getMMI();
7827 
7828  // Insert a label at the end of the invoke call to mark the try range. This
7829  // can be used to detect deletion of the invoke via the MachineModuleInfo.
7830  MCSymbol *EndLabel = MMI.getContext().createTempSymbol();
7831  Chain = DAG.getEHLabel(getCurSDLoc(), Chain, EndLabel);
7832 
7833  // Inform MachineModuleInfo of range.
7834  auto Pers = classifyEHPersonality(FuncInfo.Fn->getPersonalityFn());
7835  // There is a platform (e.g. wasm) that uses funclet style IR but does not
7836  // actually use outlined funclets and their LSDA info style.
7837  if (MF.hasEHFunclets() && isFuncletEHPersonality(Pers)) {
7838  assert(II && "II should've been set");
7839  WinEHFuncInfo *EHInfo = MF.getWinEHFuncInfo();
7840  EHInfo->addIPToStateRange(II, BeginLabel, EndLabel);
7841  } else if (!isScopedEHPersonality(Pers)) {
7842  assert(EHPadBB);
7843  MF.addInvoke(FuncInfo.MBBMap[EHPadBB], BeginLabel, EndLabel);
7844  }
7845 
7846  return Chain;
7847 }
7848 
7849 std::pair<SDValue, SDValue>
7850 SelectionDAGBuilder::lowerInvokable(TargetLowering::CallLoweringInfo &CLI,
7851  const BasicBlock *EHPadBB) {
7852  MCSymbol *BeginLabel = nullptr;
7853 
7854  if (EHPadBB) {
7855  // Both PendingLoads and PendingExports must be flushed here;
7856  // this call might not return.
7857  (void)getRoot();
7858  DAG.setRoot(lowerStartEH(getControlRoot(), EHPadBB, BeginLabel));
7859  CLI.setChain(getRoot());
7860  }
7861 
7862  const TargetLowering &TLI = DAG.getTargetLoweringInfo();
7863  std::pair<SDValue, SDValue> Result = TLI.LowerCallTo(CLI);
7864 
7865  assert((CLI.IsTailCall || Result.second.getNode()) &&
7866  "Non-null chain expected with non-tail call!");
7867  assert((Result.second.getNode() || !Result.first.getNode()) &&
7868  "Null value expected with tail call!");
7869 
7870  if (!Result.second.getNode()) {
7871  // As a special case, a null chain means that a tail call has been emitted
7872  // and the DAG root is already updated.
7873  HasTailCall = true;
7874 
7875  // Since there's no actual continuation from this block, nothing can be
7876  // relying on us setting vregs for them.
7877  PendingExports.clear();
7878  } else {
7879  DAG.setRoot(Result.second);
7880  }
7881 
7882  if (EHPadBB) {
7883  DAG.setRoot(lowerEndEH(getRoot(), cast_or_null<InvokeInst>(CLI.CB), EHPadBB,
7884  BeginLabel));
7885  }
7886 
7887  return Result;
7888 }
7889 
7890 void SelectionDAGBuilder::LowerCallTo(const CallBase &CB, SDValue Callee,
7891  bool isTailCall,
7892  bool isMustTailCall,
7893  const BasicBlock *EHPadBB) {
7894  auto &DL = DAG.getDataLayout();
7895  FunctionType *FTy = CB.getFunctionType();
7896  Type *RetTy = CB.getType();
7897 
7898  TargetLowering::ArgListTy Args;
7899  Args.reserve(CB.arg_size());
7900 
7901  const Value *SwiftErrorVal = nullptr;
7902  const TargetLowering &TLI = DAG.getTargetLoweringInfo();
7903 
7904  if (isTailCall) {
7905  // Avoid emitting tail calls in functions with the disable-tail-calls
7906  // attribute.
7907  auto *Caller = CB.getParent()->getParent();
7908  if (Caller->getFnAttribute("disable-tail-calls").getValueAsString() ==
7909  "true" && !isMustTailCall)
7910  isTailCall = false;
7911 
7912  // We can't tail call inside a function with a swifterror argument. Lowering
7913  // does not support this yet. It would have to move into the swifterror
7914  // register before the call.
7915  if (TLI.supportSwiftError() &&
7916  Caller->getAttributes().hasAttrSomewhere(Attribute::SwiftError))
7917  isTailCall = false;
7918  }
7919 
7920  for (auto I = CB.arg_begin(), E = CB.arg_end(); I != E; ++I) {
7921  TargetLowering::ArgListEntry Entry;
7922  const Value *V = *I;
7923 
7924  // Skip empty types
7925  if (V->getType()->isEmptyTy())
7926  continue;
7927 
7928  SDValue ArgNode = getValue(V);
7929  Entry.Node = ArgNode; Entry.Ty = V->getType();
7930 
7931  Entry.setAttributes(&CB, I - CB.arg_begin());
7932 
7933  // Use swifterror virtual register as input to the call.
7934  if (Entry.IsSwiftError && TLI.supportSwiftError()) {
7935  SwiftErrorVal = V;
7936  // We find the virtual register for the actual swifterror argument.
7937  // Instead of using the Value, we use the virtual register instead.
7938  Entry.Node =
7939  DAG.getRegister(SwiftError.getOrCreateVRegUseAt(&CB, FuncInfo.MBB, V),
7940  EVT(TLI.getPointerTy(DL)));
7941  }
7942 
7943  Args.push_back(Entry);
7944 
7945  // If we have an explicit sret argument that is an Instruction, (i.e., it
7946  // might point to function-local memory), we can't meaningfully tail-call.
7947  if (Entry.IsSRet && isa<Instruction>(V))
7948  isTailCall = false;
7949  }
7950 
7951  // If call site has a cfguardtarget operand bundle, create and add an
7952  // additional ArgListEntry.
7953  if (auto Bundle = CB.getOperandBundle(LLVMContext::OB_cfguardtarget)) {
7954  TargetLowering::ArgListEntry Entry;
7955  Value *V = Bundle->Inputs[0];
7956  SDValue ArgNode = getValue(V);
7957  Entry.Node = ArgNode;
7958  Entry.Ty = V->getType();
7959  Entry.IsCFGuardTarget = true;
7960  Args.push_back(Entry);
7961  }
7962 
7963  // Check if target-independent constraints permit a tail call here.
7964  // Target-dependent constraints are checked within TLI->LowerCallTo.
7965  if (isTailCall && !isInTailCallPosition(CB, DAG.getTarget()))
7966  isTailCall = false;
7967 
7968  // Disable tail calls if there is an swifterror argument. Targets have not
7969  // been updated to support tail calls.
7970  if (TLI.supportSwiftError() && SwiftErrorVal)
7971  isTailCall = false;
7972 
7973  ConstantInt *CFIType = nullptr;
7974  if (CB.isIndirectCall()) {
7975  if (auto Bundle = CB.getOperandBundle(LLVMContext::OB_kcfi)) {
7976  if (!TLI.supportKCFIBundles())
7977  report_fatal_error(
7978  "Target doesn't support calls with kcfi operand bundles.");
7979  CFIType = cast<ConstantInt>(Bundle->Inputs[0]);
7980  assert(CFIType->getType()->isIntegerTy(32) && "Invalid CFI type");
7981  }
7982  }
7983 
7984  TargetLowering::CallLoweringInfo CLI(DAG);
7985  CLI.setDebugLoc(getCurSDLoc())
7986  .setChain(getRoot())
7987  .setCallee(RetTy, FTy, Callee, std::move(Args), CB)
7988  .setTailCall(isTailCall)
7989  .setConvergent(CB.isConvergent())
7990  .setIsPreallocated(
7991  CB.countOperandBundlesOfType(LLVMContext::OB_preallocated) != 0)
7992  .setCFIType(CFIType);
7993  std::pair<SDValue, SDValue> Result = lowerInvokable(CLI, EHPadBB);
7994 
7995  if (Result.first.getNode()) {
7996  Result.first = lowerRangeToAssertZExt(DAG, CB, Result.first);
7997  setValue(&CB, Result.first);
7998  }
7999 
8000  // The last element of CLI.InVals has the SDValue for swifterror return.
8001  // Here we copy it to a virtual register and update SwiftErrorMap for
8002  // book-keeping.
8003  if (SwiftErrorVal && TLI.supportSwiftError()) {
8004  // Get the last element of InVals.
8005  SDValue Src = CLI.InVals.back();
8006  Register VReg =
8007  SwiftError.getOrCreateVRegDefAt(&CB, FuncInfo.MBB, SwiftErrorVal);
8008  SDValue CopyNode = CLI.DAG.getCopyToReg(Result.second, CLI.DL, VReg, Src);
8009  DAG.setRoot(CopyNode);
8010  }
8011 }
8012 
8013 static SDValue getMemCmpLoad(const Value *PtrVal, MVT LoadVT,
8014  SelectionDAGBuilder &Builder) {
8015  // Check to see if this load can be trivially constant folded, e.g. if the
8016  // input is from a string literal.
8017  if (const Constant *LoadInput = dyn_cast<Constant>(PtrVal)) {
8018  // Cast pointer to the type we really want to load.
8019  Type *LoadTy =
8020  Type::getIntNTy(PtrVal->getContext(), LoadVT.getScalarSizeInBits());
8021  if (LoadVT.isVector())
8022  LoadTy = FixedVectorType::get(LoadTy, LoadVT.getVectorNumElements());
8023 
8024  LoadInput = ConstantExpr::getBitCast(const_cast<Constant *>(LoadInput),
8025  PointerType::getUnqual(LoadTy));
8026 
8027  if (const Constant *LoadCst =
8028  ConstantFoldLoadFromConstPtr(const_cast<Constant *>(LoadInput),
8029  LoadTy, Builder.DAG.getDataLayout()))
8030  return Builder.getValue(LoadCst);
8031  }
8032 
8033  // Otherwise, we have to emit the load. If the pointer is to unfoldable but
8034  // still constant memory, the input chain can be the entry node.
8035  SDValue Root;
8036  bool ConstantMemory = false;
8037 
8038  // Do not serialize (non-volatile) loads of constant memory with anything.
8039  if (Builder.AA && Builder.AA->pointsToConstantMemory(PtrVal)) {
8040  Root = Builder.DAG.getEntryNode();
8041  ConstantMemory = true;
8042  } else {
8043  // Do not serialize non-volatile loads against each other.
8044  Root = Builder.DAG.getRoot();
8045  }
8046 
8047  SDValue Ptr = Builder.getValue(PtrVal);
8048  SDValue LoadVal =
8049  Builder.DAG.getLoad(LoadVT, Builder.getCurSDLoc(), Root, Ptr,
8050  MachinePointerInfo(PtrVal), Align(1));
8051 
8052  if (!ConstantMemory)
8053  Builder.PendingLoads.push_back(LoadVal.getValue(1));
8054  return LoadVal;
8055 }
8056 
8057 /// Record the value for an instruction that produces an integer result,
8058 /// converting the type where necessary.
8059 void SelectionDAGBuilder::processIntegerCallValue(const Instruction &I,
8060  SDValue Value,
8061  bool IsSigned) {
8062  EVT VT = DAG.getTargetLoweringInfo().getValueType(DAG.getDataLayout(),
8063  I.getType(), true);
8064  if (IsSigned)
8065  Value = DAG.getSExtOrTrunc(Value, getCurSDLoc(), VT);
8066  else
8067  Value = DAG.getZExtOrTrunc(Value, getCurSDLoc(), VT);
8068  setValue(&I, Value);
8069 }
8070 
8071 /// See if we can lower a memcmp/bcmp call into an optimized form. If so, return
8072 /// true and lower it. Otherwise return false, and it will be lowered like a
8073 /// normal call.
8074 /// The caller already checked that \p I calls the appropriate LibFunc with a
8075 /// correct prototype.
8076 bool SelectionDAGBuilder::visitMemCmpBCmpCall(const CallInst &I) {
8077  const Value *LHS = I.getArgOperand(0), *RHS = I.getArgOperand(1);
8078  const Value *Size = I.getArgOperand(2);
8079  const ConstantSDNode *CSize = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(getValue(Size));
8080  if (CSize && CSize->getZExtValue() == 0) {
8081  EVT CallVT = DAG.getTargetLoweringInfo().getValueType(DAG.getDataLayout(),
8082  I.getType(), true);
8083  setValue(&I, DAG.getConstant(0, getCurSDLoc(), CallVT));
8084  return true;
8085  }
8086 
8087  const SelectionDAGTargetInfo &TSI = DAG.getSelectionDAGInfo();
8088  std::pair<SDValue, SDValue> Res = TSI.EmitTargetCodeForMemcmp(
8089  DAG, getCurSDLoc(), DAG.getRoot(), getValue(LHS), getValue(RHS),
8090  getValue(Size), MachinePointerInfo(LHS), MachinePointerInfo(RHS));
8091  if (Res.first.getNode()) {
8092  processIntegerCallValue(I, Res.first, true);
8093  PendingLoads.push_back(Res.second);
8094  return true;
8095  }
8096 
8097  // memcmp(S1,S2,2) != 0 -> (*(short*)LHS != *(short*)RHS) != 0
8098  // memcmp(S1,S2,4) != 0 -> (*(int*)LHS != *(int*)RHS) != 0
8099  if (!CSize || !isOnlyUsedInZeroEqualityComparison(&I))
8100  return false;
8101 
8102  // If the target has a fast compare for the given size, it will return a
8103  // preferred load type for that size. Require that the load VT is legal and
8104  // that the target supports unaligned loads of that type. Otherwise, return
8105  // INVALID.
8106  auto hasFastLoadsAndCompare = [&](unsigned NumBits) {
8107  const TargetLowering &TLI = DAG.getTargetLoweringInfo();
8108  MVT LVT = TLI.hasFastEqualityCompare(NumBits);
8109  if (LVT != MVT::INVALID_SIMPLE_VALUE_TYPE) {
8110  // TODO: Handle 5 byte compare as 4-byte + 1 byte.
8111  // TODO: Handle 8 byte compare on x86-32 as two 32-bit loads.
8112  // TODO: Check alignment of src and dest ptrs.
8113  unsigned DstAS = LHS->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace();
8114  unsigned SrcAS = RHS->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace();
8115  if (!TLI.isTypeLegal(LVT) ||
8116  !TLI.allowsMisalignedMemoryAccesses(LVT, SrcAS) ||
8117  !TLI.allowsMisalignedMemoryAccesses(LVT, DstAS))
8118  LVT = MVT::INVALID_SIMPLE_VALUE_TYPE;
8119  }
8120 
8121  return LVT;
8122  };
8123 
8124  // This turns into unaligned loads. We only do this if the target natively
8125  // supports the MVT we'll be loading or if it is small enough (<= 4) that
8126  // we'll only produce a small number of byte loads.
8127  MVT LoadVT;
8128  unsigned NumBitsToCompare = CSize->getZExtValue() * 8;
8129  switch (NumBitsToCompare) {
8130  default:
8131  return false;
8132  case 16:
8133  LoadVT = MVT::i16;
8134  break;
8135  case 32:
8136  LoadVT = MVT::i32;
8137  break;
8138  case 64:
8139  case 128:
8140  case 256:
8141  LoadVT = hasFastLoadsAndCompare(NumBitsToCompare);
8142  break;
8143  }
8144 
8145  if (LoadVT == MVT::INVALID_SIMPLE_VALUE_TYPE)
8146  return false;
8147 
8148  SDValue LoadL = getMemCmpLoad(LHS, LoadVT, *this);
8149  SDValue LoadR = getMemCmpLoad(RHS, LoadVT, *this);
8150 
8151  // Bitcast to a wide integer type if the loads are vectors.
8152  if (LoadVT.isVector()) {
8153  EVT CmpVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(LHS->getContext(), LoadVT.getSizeInBits());
8154  LoadL = DAG.getBitcast(CmpVT, LoadL);
8155  LoadR = DAG.getBitcast(CmpVT, LoadR);
8156  }
8157 
8158  SDValue Cmp = DAG.getSetCC(getCurSDLoc(), MVT::i1, LoadL, LoadR, ISD::SETNE);
8159  processIntegerCallValue(I, Cmp, false);
8160  return true;
8161 }
8162 
8163 /// See if we can lower a memchr call into an optimized form. If so, return
8164 /// true and lower it. Otherwise return false, and it will be lowered like a
8165 /// normal call.
8166 /// The caller already checked that \p I calls the appropriate LibFunc with a
8167 /// correct prototype.
8168 bool SelectionDAGBuilder::visitMemChrCall(const CallInst &I) {
8169  const Value *Src = I.getArgOperand(0);
8170  const Value *Char = I.getArgOperand(1);
8171  const Value *Length = I.getArgOperand(2);
8172 
8173  const SelectionDAGTargetInfo &TSI = DAG.getSelectionDAGInfo();
8174  std::pair<SDValue, SDValue> Res =
8175  TSI.EmitTargetCodeForMemchr(DAG, getCurSDLoc(), DAG.getRoot(),
8176  getValue(Src), getValue(Char), getValue(Length),
8177  MachinePointerInfo(Src));
8178  if (Res.first.getNode()) {
8179  setValue(&I, Res.first);
8180  PendingLoads.push_back(Res.second);
8181  return true;
8182  }
8183 
8184  return false;
8185 }
8186 
8187 /// See if we can lower a mempcpy call into an optimized form. If so, return
8188 /// true and lower it. Otherwise return false, and it will be lowered like a
8189 /// normal call.
8190 /// The caller already checked that \p I calls the appropriate LibFunc with a
8191 /// correct prototype.
8192 bool SelectionDAGBuilder::visitMemPCpyCall(const CallInst &I) {
8193  SDValue Dst = getValue(I.getArgOperand(0));
8194  SDValue Src = getValue(I.getArgOperand(1));
8195  SDValue Size = getValue(I.getArgOperand(2));
8196 
8197  Align DstAlign = DAG.InferPtrAlign(Dst).valueOrOne();
8198  Align SrcAlign = DAG.InferPtrAlign(Src).valueOrOne();
8199  // DAG::getMemcpy needs Alignment to be defined.
8200  Align Alignment = std::min(DstAlign, SrcAlign);
8201 
8202  bool isVol = false;
8203  SDLoc sdl = getCurSDLoc();
8204 
8205  // In the mempcpy context we need to pass in a false value for isTailCall
8206  // because the return pointer needs to be adjusted by the size of
8207  // the copied memory.
8208  SDValue Root = isVol ? getRoot() : getMemoryRoot();
8209  SDValue MC = DAG.getMemcpy(Root, sdl, Dst, Src, Size, Alignment, isVol, false,
8210  /*isTailCall=*/false,
8211  MachinePointerInfo(I.getArgOperand(0)),
8212  MachinePointerInfo(I.getArgOperand(1)),
8213  I.getAAMetadata());
8214  assert(MC.getNode() != nullptr &&
8215  "** memcpy should not be lowered as TailCall in mempcpy context **");
8216  DAG.setRoot(MC);
8217 
8218  // Check if Size needs to be truncated or extended.
8219  Size = DAG.getSExtOrTrunc(Size, sdl, Dst.getValueType());
8220 
8221  // Adjust return pointer to point just past the last dst byte.
8222  SDValue DstPlusSize = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, sdl, Dst.getValueType(),
8223  Dst, Size);
8224  setValue(&I, DstPlusSize);
8225  return true;
8226 }

8228 /// See if we can lower a strcpy call into an optimized form. If so, return
8229 /// true and lower it, otherwise return false and it will be lowered like a
8230 /// normal call.

8232 /// correct prototype.
8233 bool SelectionDAGBuilder::visitStrCpyCall(const CallInst &I, bool isStpcpy) {

8235 
8236  const SelectionDAGTargetInfo &TSI = DAG.getSelectionDAGInfo();

8238  TSI.EmitTargetCodeForStrcpy(DAG, getCurSDLoc(), getRoot(),
8239  getValue(Arg0), getValue(Arg1),
8240  MachinePointerInfo(Arg0),
8241  MachinePointerInfo(Arg1), isStpcpy);
8242  if (Res.first.getNode()) {
8243  setValue(&I, Res.first);
8244  DAG.setRoot(Res.second);
8245  return true;
8246  }
8247 
8248  return false;
8249 }
